STEP 1 : Pick Alternate Digits, leaving last digit
4 2 6 3 9 8 2 6 4 0 2 6 9 2 9 9
STEP 2 : Multiply all selected digits by 2
4x2 2 6x2 3 9x2 8 2x2 6 4x2 0 2x2 6 9x2 2 9x2 9
8 2 12 3 18 8 4 6 8 0 4 6 18 2 18 9
STEP 3 : If multiplied digit is more than 9, add both the digits
8 2 1+2 3 1+8 8 4 6 8 0 4 6 1+8 2 1+8 9 8 2 3 3 9 8 4 6 8 0 4 6 9 2 9 9
STEP 4 : Add all the resulting digits
8 + 2 + 3 + 3 + 9 + 8 + 4 + 6 + 8 + 0 + 4 + 6 + 9 + 2 + 9 + 9
= 90
STEP 5 : If resulting value (= 90) is a multiple of 10,
then Luhn check is valid
